wikipedia_page.main: Dennis Windross (12 May 1938 – 9 October 1989) was an English footballer who scored 11 goals from 98 appearances in the Football League playing as a forward or wing half for Middlesbrough, Brighton & Hove Albion, Darlington and Doncaster Rovers. He was a scorer in Doncaster's record League win, by ten goals to nil against his former club Darlington on 25 January 1964.
